  <dsc><c01 id="aspace_b6fd8a91d7539fdfa7d7d5aa6390fe78" level="item"><did><unittitle>Cornell University paddle</unittitle><unitid>MU-4118</unitid><unitdate certainty="approximate" datechar="creation" normal="1931/1934" type="inclusive">1931-1934</unitdate><physdesc id="aspace_f320fc47b93cf66f2c193c8c275e6d1f">Wooden paddle with Cornell University written on one side, and signatures on the other. Signed by Edward A Reed, Peter Carnesale, and other illegible signatures.</physdesc><container id="aspace_3de5941e68e7b64ad10e43e29f4eff36" label="Mixed Materials [31924113902906]" type="mu">4118</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_588e200559d2573d39110646ed52a372" level="item"><did><unittitle>Rothschild Bros. paper Cornell pennant</unittitle><unitid>MU-747</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce">Undated</unitdate><container altrender="Flat box, (24.5w x 20.5d x 3h)" id="aspace_1e56cebaf85e6c864fcd478d900827d3" label="Realia [31924131171799]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_57b17dd910b0f29e8e85f0b166c0cd8e"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Red paper pennant with white "Cornell" on the front and "Pennants, Banners, Pillow Tops, Pictures: Rothschild Bros" on back.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_d4ea7d5c8308bbb3ffb2e3fec2fa35a9" level="item"><did><unittitle>Triangle laundry tag</unittitle><unitid>MU-1033</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce">Undated</unitdate><container altrender="Flat box, (24.5w x 20.5d x 3h)" id="aspace_73b2f232fd0c96eae8cbf845ccf1231a" label="Realia [31924131171799]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_99b71ac2130c5f9db463a54344745af8"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Canvas triangle with accompanying note: "Believed to be tag for laundry case, which was sent home to be done."</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_a527d1456aa0d0dc5c503a75aa798487" level="item"><did><unittitle>Goldfish swallowing contest net</unittitle><unitid>MU-432</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1956/1956" type="inclusive">1956</unitdate><container altrender="Flat box, (24.5w x 20.5d x 3h)" id="aspace_2ac535c946f72fae9db674011488f8ef" label="Realia [31924131171799]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_663079e19a7b9b15dcefff37f0253bd3"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Net used by Darryl R. Turgeon in winning the 1956 Goldfish Swallowing Contest at Cornell, held on the Arts Quad on November 9, 1956. He swallowed 6 fish. Includes accompanying article.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_a8e551f1921c53dd5b8da337336a6a18" level="item"><did><unittitle>Hand-drawn circular Cornell picture frame on cardboard</unittitle><unitid>MU-1361</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce">Undated</unitdate><container altrender="Flat box, (24.5w x 20.5d x 3h)" id="aspace_297dcf977f5a4a2e5614b0e21264892e" label="Realia [31924131171799]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_1e68bdb01db9feb92006741be55aafd6"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Note on back reads "Uncle Ben's Cornell frame."</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_450bb15a540cbab93f9cc78cc4013ffb" level="item"><did><unittitle>Cornell hand-made picture frame - "Cornell I yell yell yell Cornell"</unittitle><unitid>MU-1362</unitid><container altrender="Flat box, (24.5w x 20.5d x 3h)" id="aspace_f359ef088d201fb251f464da46a5dd54" label="Realia [31924131171799]" type="box">1</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_dbca51567a2638ae136df218b84ad999" level="item"><did><unittitle>Large Cornell pencil</unittitle><unitid>MU-814</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce">Undated</unitdate><container altrender="Flat box, (24.5w x 20.5d x 3h)" id="aspace_9de6a1ffb0fa4d7b5ac457f57e9ce0d9" label="Realia [31924131171799]" type="box">1</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_7eee1a341e8bb7f190c5ac30f2f45449" level="item"><did><unittitle>Paper coasters with emblem</unittitle><unitid>MU-1046</unitid><unitdate cale